# Project Import Patterns

## Prisma Client
Always use named import for prisma:

```typescript
// ✅ Correct
import { prisma } from '@/lib/prisma';

// ❌ Wrong - will cause build error
import prisma from '@/lib/prisma';
```

## Authentication
Use the auth function from lib:

```typescript
import { auth } from '@/lib/auth';

const session = await auth();
// Access club via selectedClubId, NOT clubId
const clubId = session?.user?.selectedClubId;
```

## Common Session Properties
- `session.user.id` - User ID
- `session.user.email` - User email
- `session.user.selectedClubId` - Currently selected club ID (NOT clubId)
- `session.user.role` - Platform role (PlatformRole enum)

## i18n Translations
Always import i18n.client before useTranslation:

```typescript
import '@/lib/i18n.client';
import { useTranslation } from 'react-i18next';

// In component
const { t } = useTranslation();
```

## Prisma Models - No clubId on Competition
Competition model does NOT have clubId. Filter competitions by:
- Getting competition IDs from games that belong to the club
- Or filtering by echelon

```typescript
// ✅ Correct - get competitions from club's games
const competitionIds = [...new Set(games.map(g => g.competitionId).filter(Boolean))];
const competitions = await prisma.competition.findMany({
  where: { id: { in: competitionIds as number[] } },
});

// ❌ Wrong - Competition has no clubId
const competitions = await prisma.competition.findMany({
  where: { clubId },
});
```
